            <biogHist>
                <p>Margaret or Mary MacDonald was the daughter of crofters Roderick and Marion
                    MacDonald and she appears to have remained unmarried throughout her life. She is
                    described as a weaver, cotter, general domestic servant and finally as a pauper
                    at her death. In her final years, she is recorded living with her nephew John
                    Macdonald and family.</p>
                <p>She died in Hogha Gearraidh, North Uist in 1894 after suffering from bronchitis;
                    her grand-nephew Hector MacDonald was present at the signing of her death
                    certificate.</p>
                <p>Alexander Carmichael visited Margaret MacDonald in November 1880, collecting a
                    charm from her entitled 'Eolas A Chrannachain'. </p>
